changePrice(uint256,uint256).details: can't be external because also called within newRental

collectRentAllTokens().details: makes it easy for me to call whenever I want to keep people paying their rent, thus cannot be internalcannot be external because it is called within the step1 functions, therefore public

complete().details: users pull dai into their ac   count.

depositDai(uint256,uint256).details: it is possible a user's deposit could be reduced to zero following _collectRentthey would then increase their deposit despite no longer owning itthis is ok, they can still withdraw via withdrawDeposit.

exit(uint256).details: do not need to be the current owner

liveDepositAbleToWithdraw(uint256).return: how much the current owner has deposited

rentOwed(uint256).details: called in collectRent function, and various other view functions

step1checkMarketsResolved().details: they are split into two sections due to the presence of step1BemergencyExit and step1CcircuitBreakercan be called by anyone

step2withdrawFromAugur().details: gets funds back from Augur, gets the available funds for distributioncan be called by anyone, but only once

step3payAndrew().details: this was originally included within step3 but it was modifed so that ineraction with Dai contract happened at the end

userDepositAbleToWithdraw(uint256).return: how much the current user has deposited (note: user not owner)

withdrawDeposit(uint256,uint256).details: do not need to be the current owner

withdrawDepositAfterResolution().details: the other withdraw deposit functions are locked when markets have resolved so must use this one... which can only be called if markets have resolved. This function is also different in that it does ... not attempt to collect rent or transfer ownership to a previous owner

changePrice(uint256,uint256).notice: increase the price of an existing rental

collectRentAllTokens().notice: /////////// ORDINARY COURSE OF BUSINESS FUNCTIONS- EXTERNALS //////////////collects rent for all tokens

complete().notice: the final function of the competition resolution process. Pays out winnings, or returns funds, as necessary

depositDai(uint256,uint256).notice: add new dai deposit to an existing rental

step1BemergencyExit().notice: emergency function in case the augur markets never resolve for whatever reasonreturns all funds to all userscan only be called 6 months after augur markets should have ended

step1CcircuitBreaker().notice: Same as above, except that only I can call it, and I can call it wheneverto be clear, this only allows me to return all funds. I can not set a winner.

step1checkMarketsResolved().notice: /////////// MARKET RESOLUTION FUNCTIONS ////////////// the first of three functions which must be called, one after the other, to conclude the competitionwinnings can be paid out (or funds returned) only when these two steps are completedthis function checks whether the Augur markets have resolved, and if yes, whether they resolved correct or not

step2withdrawFromAugur().notice: the second of the three functions which must be called, one after the other, to conclude the competition

step3payAndrew().notice: the final of the three functions which must be called, one after the other, to conclude the competitionpays me my 1% if markets resolved correctly. If not I don't deserve shit

withdrawDepositAfterResolution().notice: withdraw full deposit after markets have resolved
